chipGenProduct.name: chipGenProduct
chipGenProduct.description: The product type represented by this agent.

chipGenServiceDate.name: chipGenServiceDate
chipGenServiceDate.description: The date that the product was last serviced in the format yymmdd. If this date is unknown, the value of this object is '000000'.

chipGenNetman.name: chipGenNetman
chipGenNetman.description: The IP (source) Address of the last authenticated SNMP PDU received by this entity before this request. An IP Address of 00.00.00.00 represents the default value.

chipGenDiagnostics.name: chipGenDiagnostics
chipGenDiagnostics.description: The result of this product's diagnostic test(s). If any test fails, this will have the failed(2) value. Note, many products do not operate after a diagnostic failure. In this case, no SNMP communication would be available.

chipGenSerial.name: chipGenSerial
chipGenSerial.description: The serial number of this product.

chipGenID.name: chipGenID
chipGenID.description: A unique ID used for grouping disparate agents together. For example, a concentrator may contain multiple agents. This ID is could be assigned by the management station to identify all of these agents as being contained in the same concentrator.

chipGenVers.name: chipGenVers
chipGenVers.description: The version identifier(s) for this agent.

chipGenAuthFailureAddr.name: chipGenAuthFailureAddr
chipGenAuthFailureAddr.description: The source IP Address of the last SNMP request that caused an authentication failure trap to be generated. This object is also included in the SNMP authenticationFailure trap.

chipGenTimeLastChanged.name: chipGenTimeLastChanged
chipGenTimeLastChanged.description: A snapshot of sysUpTime when the last trap was generated. This attribute can be used to save polling by a management station. If there have been no traps generated since the last poll, there is no need for the station to poll again.

chipEchoStart.name: chipEchoStart
chipEchoStart.description: Setting chipEchoStart to startEcho(2) causes the device to begin an ICMP echo sequence using the parameters indicated by the rest of the chipEcho group.

chipEchoAddr.name: chipEchoAddr
chipEchoAddr.description: The IP Address to which the device will ping. This object can only be set to valid unicast class A, class B, or class C addresses. The default IP Address is loopback (127.0.0.1).

chipEchoPattern.name: chipEchoPattern
chipEchoPattern.description: The actual pattern to be contained in the ICMP echo packet.

chipEchoNumber.name: chipEchoNumber
chipEchoNumber.description: The number of ICMP echo packets (pings) to send.

chipEchoSize.name: chipEchoSize
chipEchoSize.description: The size of the ICMP echo packet (ping) to send when chipEchoStart is set. The valid range is between 64 and 1500 octets.

chipEchoResponseCounts.name: chipEchoResponseCounts
chipEchoResponseCounts.description: The count of ICMP echo response packets received since the last PING was initiated.

olAgentsMySlot.name: olAgentsMySlot
olAgentsMySlot.description: The slot id of this agent.

olAgentsMasterReset.name: olAgentsMasterReset
olAgentsMasterReset.description: Resetting mastership causes a new mastership election to occur. The agent with the highest mastership priority will become the new master. If there is more than one agent with the highest priority, the selection between those agents will be arbritrary.

olAgentsTable.name: olAgentsTable
olAgentsTable.description: A table of agents in the concentrator as seen by this agent. A master will see all the agents; a slave will only see itself.

olAgentsEntry.name: olAgentsEntry
olAgentsEntry.description: A profile of an agent within the concentrator.

olAgentsSlotIndex.name: olAgentsSlotIndex
olAgentsSlotIndex.description: The slot number that identifies the referenced agent.

olAgentsStationAddr.name: olAgentsStationAddr
olAgentsStationAddr.description: The unique identifier for this agent. Often this is the value of ifPhysAddress for the first interface.

olAgentsIpAddress.name: olAgentsIpAddress
olAgentsIpAddress.description: An IP Address that can be used to communicate to this agent. Note, this object's value may change as the agent switches to different sub-networks.

olAgentsMasterStatus.name: olAgentsMasterStatus
olAgentsMasterStatus.description: The mastership status of this agent.

olAgentsMasterPriority.name: olAgentsMasterPriority
olAgentsMasterPriority.description: The mastership priority of this agent. Ten is the highest and one is the lowest. Never means will not be able become master. Some agents do not have the capability to become master (the etherent to ethernet bridge, e.g.) and setting those agents to a value other than never(11) will generate an invalid value error. Priority is only used when an election occurs. Mastership is not pre-emptive; use the reset mastership command (olAgentsMasterReset).

ocAgentsSubSlot.name: ocAgentsSubSlot
ocAgentsSubSlot.description: The subslot index for this agent. For agents not located in the ONcore system, this object will always return 1 for this object value.

olConcType.name: olConcType
olConcType.description: This object identifies the type of concentrator represented by this agent.

olConcReset.name: olConcReset
olConcReset.description: Setting this value to reset(2) causes this concentrator to reset.

olConcNumSlots.name: olConcNumSlots
olConcNumSlots.description: The number of slots in this concentrator. This value is the sum total of all payload slots plus any slots reserved for controller modules. For example, for an ONcore agent operating in a 17-slot ONcore hub, this object will have the value 19 (17 payload slots plus 2 controller slots). Similarly, if an ONline hub contains a hidden controller, then this object will have the value 7 (the hidden controller does not actually occupy a main slot in the 6-slot concentrator, but it will report itself as slot 7). Also, for an ONline agent operating in an ONcore hub, this object's value will not exceed 17.

olConcProfile.name: olConcProfile
olConcProfile.description: A bit string where the least significant bit corresponds to slot 1. A '1' in the bit indicates that a module is present in that slot. The number of octets provided is based on the olConcNumSlots value divided by 8. Any extra bits (for example, bits 18-24 for 17 slots) are meaningless. For example, the string 0x01 0xFF 0xFF would represent a full 17 slot concentrator.

olEnvTempStatus.name: olEnvTempStatus
olEnvTempStatus.description: The overall temperature status for this concentrator. This object's value is an aggregate of all the temperature probes in the concentrator, such that, when at least one probe reports extreme temperature, this object will have the value extremeTemp(2). This object will have the value warning(3) prior to reporting the value extremeTemp(2) as a means of warning of a possible hub overheat condition.

olEnvPSCapacity.name: olEnvPSCapacity
olEnvPSCapacity.description: The total capacity of power supplies for this concentrator.

olEnvPSTable.name: olEnvPSTable
olEnvPSTable.description: A table that contains information about each potential power supply in the concentrator.

olEnvPSEntry.name: olEnvPSEntry
olEnvPSEntry.description: A list of information for each power supply in the concentrator.

olEnvPSIndex.name: olEnvPSIndex
olEnvPSIndex.description: Identifies the power supply for which this entry contains power supply information. For systems with the primary and backup power supply (as opposed to the N+1 design), index 1 refers to the primary, and index 2 refers to the backup.

olEnvPSAdminState.name: olEnvPSAdminState
olEnvPSAdminState.description: The current desired state of the power supply. A power supply in standby does not provide power to the concentrator. Note, in a Load Sharing Hub, this object is read only.

olEnvPSOperStatus.name: olEnvPSOperStatus
olEnvPSOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the power supply. A power supply in standby does not provide power to the concentrator.

olEnvFanStatus.name: olEnvFanStatus
olEnvFanStatus.description: The overall status of the fan(s). When fan operational status is known, this object's value is an aggregate of all fan status in the concentrator such that, when at least one fan unit is faulty, this object will have the value faulty(2).

olEnvTable.name: olEnvTable
olEnvTable.description: A table that contains information about the concentrator environment.

olEnvEntry.name: olEnvEntry
olEnvEntry.description: A list of information for each monitored component in this concentrator.

olEnvType.name: olEnvType
olEnvType.description: The type of hardware component monitored in this concentrator.

olEnvStatus.name: olEnvStatus
olEnvStatus.description: The status of the monitored hardware component.

olModTable.name: olModTable
olModTable.description: A table that contains generic information about every module that is present within the concentrator. If the concentrator is the ONcore Hub, then only the motherboard is present in this table.

olModEntry.name: olModEntry
olModEntry.description: A list of information for each module in the concentrator. If the concentrator is the ONcore Hub, then only the motherboard is present in this table.

olModSlotIndex.name: olModSlotIndex
olModSlotIndex.description: The unique slot number of this module. Its value ranges between 1 and olConcNumSlots and remains constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

olModType.name: olModType
olModType.description: The unique type identifier for this module. This type is used to identify the branch in olSpecMods (see below). module-unmanageable(1) means that only the following objects are valid for this module: olModSlotIndex olModClass olModVersion olModVendor olModReset olModConfigToDips olModConfigured module-unknown(2) means that all the generic attributes are manageable, but there is no olSpecMods branch for this module as viewed by this agent.

olModClass.name: olModClass
olModClass.description: The class of this module. Generally speaking, this object indicates the kind of module. Specifically, the class identifier specifies the internal representation of the module's managed information base.

olModDescr.name: olModDescr
olModDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the module.

olModVersion.name: olModVersion
olModVersion.description: The software version number of this module.

olModVendor.name: olModVendor
olModVendor.description: The actual manufacturer of this board.

olModResetModule.name: olModResetModule
olModResetModule.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes this module to reset.

olModConfigToDips.name: olModConfigToDips
olModConfigToDips.description: Setting this object to configure(2) causes this module to configure based on the dip switch settings.

olModConfigured.name: olModConfigured
olModConfigured.description: This object indicates whether this module has already been configured. An unconfigured module is configured to a safe state where the network is isolated and the ports are disabled.

olModNetwork.name: olModNetwork
olModNetwork.description: The network that this module is attached to. If the value is other(1) or port-switching(3), setting this object to a different value will generate the invalidData error. If the value is port-switching(3), manage the networks via the olPortNetwork object. The value per-connector(20) is returned if the managed module is a per-connector switchable and the connectors are on different networks. The connector networks are managed by the objects defined in the olSpecMods branch specified for this module. Modules and ports on the same network intercommunicate. Setting the module to isolated(2) (or other isolated values), removes this module from the backplane. Setting this module to a value that is not the same protocol type will return an invalidData error. Setting this module to a value that it does not support will return an invalidData error.

olModNetworkType.name: olModNetworkType
olModNetworkType.description: The network type of this module. port-switching(3) means that the network type differs depending on the port (like the router module). The network type reflects the valid values for olModNetwork.

olModNumPorts.name: olModNumPorts
olModNumPorts.description: The number of ports on this module. Note, ports may be physical ports like 10BASE-T ports, or logical, like the bridge module ports.

olModNumTrunks.name: olModNumTrunks
olModNumTrunks.description: The number of trunks on this module. Note, trunks are links that are, by definition, backbone connections. Examples of trunks are ring in and ring out ports for token ring, and the connections for rings to the backplane.

olPortTable.name: olPortTable
olPortTable.description: A table that contains generic information about each port on each module present within the concentrator.

olPortEntry.name: olPortEntry
olPortEntry.description: A list of information about each port in the concentrator.

olPortSlotIndex.name: olPortSlotIndex
olPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this port's module.

olPortIndex.name: olPortIndex
olPortIndex.description: The port number of this port within this module.

olPortType.name: olPortType
olPortType.description: The type of port. logical(1) is used to manage port resources that may not map directly to physical connections. The OEBM, for example, has two logical ports, although those two ports can be assigned to different combinations of four physical connections. media(2) refers to ports such as those on the 10BASE-T module.

olPortConnector.name: olPortConnector
olPortConnector.description: The connector type of this port.

olPortAdminState.name: olPortAdminState
olPortAdminState.description: The desired state of this port. Setting a port to be redundant-primary(3) or redundant-backup requires that the buddy slot and buddy port also be set to valid values (see appropriate olSpecMods objects). If the values associated with the redundant buddys are not valid, a genError will be returned. If the port is already redundant, an invalid set may result in both ports being disabled.

olPortNetwork.name: olPortNetwork
olPortNetwork.description: The network that this port is attached to. If the value of olPortNetwork is per-module(4), then use the olModNetwork to manage this port. Setting olPortNetwork to a different value in this case will generate the invalidData error. Setting this port to a value that is not the same protocol type will return invalidData error. front-panel(5) is used for modules that have a logical port and a physical front connection. An example of this is the Eth2Eth Bridge module. Setting this port to a value that it does not support will generate an invalidData error.

olPortNetworkType.name: olPortNetworkType
olPortNetworkType.description: The network type of this port. The type reflects the valid values for olPortNetwork.

olPortAlertFilter.name: olPortAlertFilter
olPortAlertFilter.description: Enabling this object for a port will allow the generation of port up (or port down) traps for port status transitions caused by end stations powering up (or down). Disabling this object will suppress the generation of port up (or port down) traps for a port. Note that this object is used in the trap generation decision only if chipAlertMode, an object in chipAlertTable, is set to filter(3). Some ports, such as integrated bridge or router ports do not support this feature. A getRequest on one of these types of ports will return a value of other(3), and a setRequest to enable(1) or disable(2) will return the invalidData object.

olTrunkTable.name: olTrunkTable
olTrunkTable.description: A table that contains generic information about each trunk on each module present within the concentrator.

olTrunkEntry.name: olTrunkEntry
olTrunkEntry.description: A list of information about each trunk in the concentrator.

olTrunkSlotIndex.name: olTrunkSlotIndex
olTrunkSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this trunk's module.

olTrunkIndex.name: olTrunkIndex
olTrunkIndex.description: The trunk number of this trunk.

olTrunkType.name: olTrunkType
olTrunkType.description: The type of trunk. ringIn(3) and ringOut(4) refer to special trunks on the token ring protocol type modules.

olTrunkConnector.name: olTrunkConnector
olTrunkConnector.description: The connector type of this trunk.

olTrunkAdminState.name: olTrunkAdminState
olTrunkAdminState.description: The desired state of this trunk. Enabling a trunk allows the trunk to pass network traffic. This object may be used to configure fiber trunk redundancy. Setting a trunk to be redundant-primary(3) or redundant-backup(4) requires that the buddy slot be previously set to a valid value (see appropriate olSpecMods objects). If fiber trunk redundancy is already configured, setting this object to a redundant state will remove the previous configuration.

olTrunkWrapState.name: olTrunkWrapState
olTrunkWrapState.description: The wrap state of this trunk. A trunk can wrap in response to a network event such as a break in the cable.

olTrunkNeighbor.name: olTrunkNeighbor
olTrunkNeighbor.description: The upstream or downstream neighbor of the trunk.

ol50nnMCTLModTable.name: ol50nnMCTLModTable
ol50nnMCTLModTable.description: A table that contains information about each 50nnM-CTL in the concentrator. Note, current architecture will limit the number of instances to one per concentrator.

ol50nnMCTLModEntry.name: ol50nnMCTLModEntry
ol50nnMCTLModEntry.description: A list of information for each 50nnM-CTL module in the concentrator.

ol50nnMCTLModSlotIndex.name: ol50nnMCTLModSlotIndex
ol50nnMCTLModSlotIndex.description: The slot number for this module.

ol50nnMCTLModTempStatus.name: ol50nnMCTLModTempStatus
ol50nnMCTLModTempStatus.description: The temperature as detected by the probes on this module.

ol51nnMMGTModTable.name: ol51nnMMGTModTable
ol51nnMMGTModTable.description: A table that contains module information about each EMM module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMMGTModEntry.name: ol51nnMMGTModEntry
ol51nnMMGTModEntry.description: A list of module information for a particular EMM module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMMGTModSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMMGTModSlotIndex
ol51nnMMGTModSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this module.

ol51nnMMGTModMasterPriority.name: ol51nnMMGTModMasterPriority
ol51nnMMGTModMasterPriority.description: The mastership priority of this agent. Ten is the highest and one is the lowest. Priority is only used when an election occurs. Mastership is not preemptive unless the reset mastership command is used.

ol51nnMMGTModMasterStatus.name: ol51nnMMGTModMasterStatus
ol51nnMMGTModMasterStatus.description: The mastership status of this agent.

ol51nnMMGTModStationAddr.name: ol51nnMMGTModStationAddr
ol51nnMMGTModStationAddr.description: A 6 octet address that uniquely identifies this module. The station address is the mac address of port 1. Note that EMMs before v3.0 will have 00-00-00-00-00-00 as their station address.

ol51nnMMGTPortTable.name: ol51nnMMGTPortTable
ol51nnMMGTPortTable.description: A table of information that contains port-specific information for each port on each 51nnM-MGT module.

ol51nnMMGTPortEntry.name: ol51nnMMGTPortEntry
ol51nnMMGTPortEntry.description: A list of information about a specific port on a 51nnM-MGT module.

ol51nnMMGTPortSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMMGTPortSlotIndex
ol51nnMMGTPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this port's module.

ol51nnMMGTPortIndex.name: ol51nnMMGTPortIndex
ol51nnMMGTPortIndex.description: The port number of this port.

ol51nnMMGTIpAddress.name: ol51nnMMGTIpAddress
ol51nnMMGTIpAddress.description: The IP Address associated with this port.

ol51nnMFIBModTable.name: ol51nnMFIBModTable
ol51nnMFIBModTable.description: A table of module-specific information for each 51nnM-FIB module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMFIBModEntry.name: ol51nnMFIBModEntry
ol51nnMFIBModEntry.description: A list of module-specific information associated with a particular 51nnM-FIB module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMFIBModSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMFIBModSlotIndex
ol51nnMFIBModSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this module.

ol51nnMFIBModDipNetwork.name: ol51nnMFIBModDipNetwork
ol51nnMFIBModDipNetwork.description: The network indicated by the module's dip switches.

ol51nnMFIBModLLW.name: ol51nnMFIBModLLW
ol51nnMFIBModLLW.description: The current state of this module's low light warning configuration. Enabling this feature causes the module to check for low light and to issue a warning if low light is present. Disabling low light has the advantage of faster redundancy switchover in the event of a port error.

ol51nnMFIBModDipLLW.name: ol51nnMFIBModDipLLW
ol51nnMFIBModDipLLW.description: The low light warning configuration indicated by this module's dip switches.

ol51nnMFIBPortTable.name: ol51nnMFIBPortTable
ol51nnMFIBPortTable.description: A table of port-specific information for each port of each 51nnM-FIB module.

ol51nnMFIBPortEntry.name: ol51nnMFIBPortEntry
ol51nnMFIBPortEntry.description: A list of information about a specific port on a 51nnM-FIB module.

ol51nnMFIBPortSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMFIBPortSlotIndex
ol51nnMFIBPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this port's module.

ol51nnMFIBPortIndex.name: ol51nnMFIBPortIndex
ol51nnMFIBPortIndex.description: The port number of this port.

ol51nnMFIBPortAdminState.name: ol51nnMFIBPortAdminState
ol51nnMFIBPortAdminState.description: The desired state of this port. Setting this port to be redundant with invalid settings of buddy slot and buddy port will return the genError error.

ol51nnMFIBPortBuddySlot.name: ol51nnMFIBPortBuddySlot
ol51nnMFIBPortBuddySlot.description: The slot index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMFIBPortBuddyPort.name: ol51nnMFIBPortBuddyPort
ol51nnMFIBPortBuddyPort.description: The port index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMFIBPortDipAdminState.name: ol51nnMFIBPortDipAdminState
ol51nnMFIBPortDipAdminState.description: The state of this port as indicated by the port's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPModTable.name: ol51nnMUTPModTable
ol51nnMUTPModTable.description: A list of module-specific information associated with a particular 51nnM-UTP module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMUTPModEntry.name: ol51nnMUTPModEntry
ol51nnMUTPModEntry.description: A module entry containing objects that describe the module level for that particular module.

ol51nnMUTPModSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMUTPModSlotIndex
ol51nnMUTPModSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this module.

ol51nnMUTPModDipNetwork.name: ol51nnMUTPModDipNetwork
ol51nnMUTPModDipNetwork.description: The network indicated by the module's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPModCrossover.name: ol51nnMUTPModCrossover
ol51nnMUTPModCrossover.description: The current state of this module's crossover configuration. Setting this object to uncrossed(2) allows the last port to be used to connect to another repeater. Often this feature is used to connect one 10BASE-T module to another.

ol51nnMUTPModDipCrossover.name: ol51nnMUTPModDipCrossover
ol51nnMUTPModDipCrossover.description: The crossover configuration indicated by this module's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPModFFL.name: ol51nnMUTPModFFL
ol51nnMUTPModFFL.description: The number of bits to store in the repeater's fifo buffer. See the module user's guide for more information.

ol51nnMUTPModDipFFL.name: ol51nnMUTPModDipFFL
ol51nnMUTPModDipFFL.description: The fifo fill level as indicated by this module's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPPortTable.name: ol51nnMUTPPortTable
ol51nnMUTPPortTable.description: A table of port-specific information for each port of this module type.

ol51nnMUTPPortEntry.name: ol51nnMUTPPortEntry
ol51nnMUTPPortEntry.description: A port entry containing objects that describe this port.

ol51nnMUTPPortSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMUTPPortSlotIndex
ol51nnMUTPPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this port's module.

ol51nnMUTPPortIndex.name: ol51nnMUTPPortIndex
ol51nnMUTPPortIndex.description: The port number of this port.

ol51nnMUTPPortAdminState.name: ol51nnMUTPPortAdminState
ol51nnMUTPPortAdminState.description: The desired state of this port. Setting this port to be redundant with invalid settings of buddy slot and buddy port will return the genError error.

ol51nnMUTPPortBuddySlot.name: ol51nnMUTPPortBuddySlot
ol51nnMUTPPortBuddySlot.description: The slot index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMUTPPortBuddyPort.name: ol51nnMUTPPortBuddyPort
ol51nnMUTPPortBuddyPort.description: The port index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMUTPPortDipAdminState.name: ol51nnMUTPPortDipAdminState
ol51nnMUTPPortDipAdminState.description: The state of this port as indicated by the port's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPPortLinkInteg.name: ol51nnMUTPPortLinkInteg
ol51nnMUTPPortLinkInteg.description: The port's link integrity configuration. Enabling link integrity configures the port to conform to the link integrity feature as specified by 10BASE-T.

ol51nnMUTPPortDipLinkInteg.name: ol51nnMUTPPortDipLinkInteg
ol51nnMUTPPortDipLinkInteg.description: The link integrity configuration as indicated by this port's dip switches.

ol51nnMUTPPortSquelch.name: ol51nnMUTPPortSquelch
ol51nnMUTPPortSquelch.description: The port's squelch configuration. See the module's user's guide for more information.

ol51nnMUTPPortDipSquelch.name: ol51nnMUTPPortDipSquelch
ol51nnMUTPPortDipSquelch.description: The port's squelch configuration as indicated by this port's dip switches.

ol51nnMTPModTable.name: ol51nnMTPModTable
ol51nnMTPModTable.description: A table of module-specific information for each 51nnM-TP module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMTPModEntry.name: ol51nnMTPModEntry
ol51nnMTPModEntry.description: A list of module-specific information about a specific 51nnM-TP module in the concentrator.

ol51nnMTPModSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMTPModSlotIndex
ol51nnMTPModSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this module.

ol51nnMTPModDipNetwork.name: ol51nnMTPModDipNetwork
ol51nnMTPModDipNetwork.description: The network indicated by the module's dip switches.

ol51nnMTPModCrossover.name: ol51nnMTPModCrossover
ol51nnMTPModCrossover.description: The current state of this module's crossover configuration. Setting this object to uncrossed(2) allows the last port to be used to connect to another repeater. Often this feature is used to connect one 10BASE-T module to another.

ol51nnMTPModDipCrossover.name: ol51nnMTPModDipCrossover
ol51nnMTPModDipCrossover.description: The crossover configuration indicated by this module's dip switches.

ol51nnMTPPortTable.name: ol51nnMTPPortTable
ol51nnMTPPortTable.description: A table of port-specific information for each port of this module type.

ol51nnMTPPortEntry.name: ol51nnMTPPortEntry
ol51nnMTPPortEntry.description: A port entry containing objects that describe this port.

ol51nnMTPPortSlotIndex.name: ol51nnMTPPortSlotIndex
ol51nnMTPPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of this port's module.

ol51nnMTPPortIndex.name: ol51nnMTPPortIndex
ol51nnMTPPortIndex.description: The port number of this port.

ol51nnMTPPortAdminState.name: ol51nnMTPPortAdminState
ol51nnMTPPortAdminState.description: The desired state of this port. Setting this port to be redundant with invalid settings of buddy slot and buddy port will return the genError error.

ol51nnMTPPortBuddySlot.name: ol51nnMTPPortBuddySlot
ol51nnMTPPortBuddySlot.description: The slot index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMTPPortBuddyPort.name: ol51nnMTPPortBuddyPort
ol51nnMTPPortBuddyPort.description: The port index of the redundant port's buddy. To set a port to be redundant, the buddy's slot and port must be set to valid values. The buddy is automatically set to be redundant to this port.

ol51nnMTPPortDipAdminState.name: ol51nnMTPPortDipAdminState
ol51nnMTPPortDipAdminState.description: The state of this port as indicated by the port's dip switches.

ol51nnMTPPortLinkInteg.name: ol51nnMTPPortLinkInteg
ol51nnMTPPortLinkInteg.description: The port's link integrity configuration. Enabling link integrity configures the port to conform to the link integrity feature as specified by 10BASE-T.

ol51nnMTPPortDipLinkInteg.name: ol51nnMTPPortDipLinkInteg
ol51nnMTPPortDipLinkInteg.description: The link integrity configuration as indicated by this port's dip switches.

ol51nnMTPPortSquelch.name: ol51nnMTPPortSquelch
ol51nnMTPPortSquelch.description: The port's squelch configuration. See the module's user's guide for more information.

ol51nnMTPPortDipSquelch.name: ol51nnMTPPortDipSquelch
ol51nnMTPPortDipSquelch.description: The port's squelch configuration as indicated by this port's dip switches.

The mapping logic will not operate on trunks which are set to external. This prevents incorrect mapping which can occur when a module in one hub detects the mapping signal from another hub. This attribute only applies to copper ring-in trunks.

ol5208MTPTrunkExtBcnRecovery.name: ol5208MTPTrunkExtBcnRecovery
ol5208MTPTrunkExtBcnRecovery.description: Indicates whether the trunk is connected to a segment that will perform beacon recovery. This should be set to exists(1) for trunks which connect to hubs which perform beacon recovery. This attribute is used to determine the fault domain when resolving a beaconing condition. The beacon recovery process will resolve beaconing on trunks with this attribute set to nonExists(2) before trunks with the attribute set to exists(1) are resolved. For backplane trunks, setting to a value other than notApplicable will return invalidData error. The default value is nonExists(2).

ol52nnMFRTrunkNetMapState.description: The map state of the copper ring-in trunk. This should be set to external for ring-in trunks which connect to external hubs. The mapping logic will not operate on trunks which are set to external. This prevents incorrect mapping which can occur when a module in one hub detects the mapping signal from another hub. This attribute only applies to copper ring-in trunks.

ol52nnMFRTrunkExtBcnRecovery.name: ol52nnMFRTrunkExtBcnRecovery
ol52nnMFRTrunkExtBcnRecovery.description: Indicates whether the trunk is connected to a segment that will perform beacon recovery. This should be set to exists(1) for trunks which connect to hubs which perform beacon recovery. This attribute is used to determine the fault domain when resolving a beaconing condition. The beacon recovery process will resolve beaconing on trunks with this attribute set to nonExists(2) before trunks with the attribute set to exists(1) are resolved. For backplane trunks, setting to a value other than notApplicable will return invalidData error. The default value is nonExists(2).

ol52nnMFRTrunkBuddySlot.name: ol52nnMFRTrunkBuddySlot
ol52nnMFRTrunkBuddySlot.description: The slot index of the redundant trunk's buddy. To set a trunk to be redundant, the buddy's slot must be set to a valid value. Copper and backplane trunks will return invdata(6). If both the ring-in and ring-out trunks of a module are configured for redundancy, they must both be redundant to the same module. The buddy slot object for this slot is automatically set to this trunk.

ol52nnMFRTrunkAdminState.name: ol52nnMFRTrunkAdminState
ol52nnMFRTrunkAdminState.description: The desired state of this trunk. Enabling a trunk allows the trunk to pass network traffic. This object may be used to configure fiber trunk redundancy. Setting a trunk to be redundant-primary(3) or redundant-backup(4) requires that the ol52nnMFRTrunkBuddySlot object be set to a valid value. If fiber trunk redundancy is already configured, setting this object to a redundant state will remove the previous configuration.

ol53nnMMGTPortConnectState.description: An indication of the connect state of this PORT. Basically, this gives a higher level view of the state of the connection by grouping PCM states and the PC-Withhold flag state. ol41nnHMTPModIpAddress.name: ol41nnHMTPModIpAddress

ol41nnHETPPortTable.description: A table of port-specific information for each port of this module type.

ol41nnHETPPortEntry.description: A port entry containing objects that describe this port.

ol41nnHETPPortSlotIndex.description: The slot (stack) number of this port's module.

ol41nnHETPPortIndex.name: ol41nnHETPPortIndex

ol41nnHETPPortReset.description: Used to reset the port's '802.3 state machine', which will re-enable a disabled port and/or reconnect a partitioned port.

olModSummaryTable.name: olModSummaryTable
olModSummaryTable.description: A table of condensed module information.

olModSummaryEntry.name: olModSummaryEntry
olModSummaryEntry.description: A summary of all the generic and value added information associated with this module.

olModSummarySlotIndex.name: olModSummarySlotIndex
olModSummarySlotIndex.description: The slot number of this module that this summary pertains to.

olModSummaryInfo.name: olModSummaryInfo
olModSummaryInfo.description: A summary of all information relating to this module in condensed format. The condensed format is only as large as needed to hence the largest value which usually is one octet. The TCP port for the terminal server, however, uses 4 octets. The summary consists of a header, a module portion, a port portion, and a trunk portion. Each portion consists of generic information and module specific information. For example, the module information consists of the olModTable entry for this slot and the olSpecMods module table information for this module type for this slot. --------------------------------------------------- The header consists of the following octets: Version of structure : 1 Number of octets in generic module Number of octets in specific module Number of octets in generic port Number of octets in specific port Number of octets in generic trunk Number of octets in specific trunk The format of the data portion is as follows: Some of the olModTable: olModType olModClass olModDescr olModVersion olModNetwork olModNetworkType olModStatus olModNumPorts olModNumTrunks olSpecMods module table (for this module) Not including slot number. For each port: Some of the olPortTable: olPortType olPortConnector olPortStatus olPortAdminState olPortNetwork olPortNetworkType olPortAlertFilter olSpecMods port table (for this port's module) Not including slot and port number. For each trunk: Some of the olTrunkTable: olTrunkType olTrunkConnector olTrunkStatus olTrunkAdminState olTrunkWrapState olTrunkNeighbor olSpecMods trunk table (for this trunk's module) Not including slot and trunk number. --------------------------------------------------- Version 2 of the summary structure: Version 2 is returned only when there is a possibility of multiple modules per slot. This is a function of the platform (concentrator). The ONcore platform is an example of this. ONline modules in the ONcore platform will still be represented by version 1 structure. Version 2 is an array of version 1 structures, Version: 2 Maximum number of v1 structures = 8. Number of v1 structures to follow => max of 8. Reserved octet = 0. 2 octets each describing the length of v1 summaries: Number of octets in summary #1. Number of octets in summary #2. Number of octets in summary #3. Number of octets in summary #4. Number of octets in summary #5. Number of octets in summary #6. Number of octets in summary #7. Number of octets in summary #8. Array of Version 1 structures. For example, there are 3 modules in slot 5, in subslot locations 1, 3 and 8. Byte Description ---- ----------- 1 Version = 2 2 Max number of v1 structures (8) 3 Number of v1 structures (3) 4 Reserved (0) 5&6 Number of bytes N(1) 7&8 Number of bytes N(2) = 0 9&10 Number of bytes N(3) 11&12 Number of bytes N(4) = 0 13&14 Number of bytes N(4) = 0 15&16 Number of bytes N(4) = 0 17&18 Number of bytes N(4) = 0 19&20 Number of bytes N(4) 21 to Version 1 summary for module in sslot 1 21 + N(1) 21 + N(1) to Version 1 summary for module in sslot 3 (21 + N(1)) + N(3) (21 + N(1)) + N(3) to Version 1 summary for module in sslot 8 ((21 + N(1)) + N(3)) + N(8) 21 to 21 + N(1) Version 1 summary for module in sslot 1 ---------------------------------------------------- In all of the above, the index for all of these tables is condensed out of the summary.

ocModTable.name: ocModTable
ocModTable.description: A table that contains generic information about every module that is present within the concentrator.

ocModEntry.name: ocModEntry
ocModEntry.description: A list of information for each module in the concentrator.

ocModSlotIndex.name: ocModSlotIndex
ocModSlotIndex.description: The unique slot number of this module. Its value ranges between 1 and olConcNumSlots and remains constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ocModSubSlotIndex.name: ocModSubSlotIndex
ocModSubSlotIndex.description: The unique subslot number of this module. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ocModNumSubSlots for the mother board in this slot (ocModNumSubSlots.<slot>.1), and it remains constant between re-initializations of the mother board. The mother board is ALWAYS the first subslot index in any particular slot. Not all subslots must be occupied, and an empty subslot will not return an instance.

ocModType.name: ocModType
ocModType.description: The unique type identifier for this module. This type is used to identify the branch in olSpecMods (see below). module-unmanageable(1) means that only the following objects are valid for this module: ocModSlotIndex ocModClass ocModVersion ocModVendor ocModReset ocModConfigToDips ocModConfigured module-unknown(2) means that all the generic attributes are manageable, but there is no olSpecMods branch for this module as viewed by this agent.

ocModClass.name: ocModClass
ocModClass.description: The class of this module. The class defines the internal data structure used to manage this module.

ocModDescr.name: ocModDescr
ocModDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the module.

ocModVersion.name: ocModVersion
ocModVersion.description: The software version number of this module.

ocModResetModule.name: ocModResetModule
ocModResetModule.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes this module to reset.

ocModConfigToDips.name: ocModConfigToDips
ocModConfigToDips.description: Setting this object to configure(2) causes this module to configure based on the dip switch settings. Note, if the NV dip switch (if applicable) is set to configure from NV, then the module will retrieve its configuration from the on-board non-volatile storage.

ocModConfigured.name: ocModConfigured
ocModConfigured.description: This object indicates whether this module has already been configured. An unconfigured module is configured to a safe state (ports are disabled and the module is isolated from the backplane networks).

ocModNetwork.name: ocModNetwork
ocModNetwork.description: The network that this module is attached to. Setting this module to a value that it does not support will return an invalidData error.

ocModNetworkType.name: ocModNetworkType
ocModNetworkType.description: The network type of this module. The network type reflects the valid values for ocModNetwork.

ocModNumPorts.name: ocModNumPorts
ocModNumPorts.description: The number of ports on this module. Note, ports may be physical ports like 10BASE-T ports, or logical, like the bridge module ports.

ocModNumTrunks.name: ocModNumTrunks
ocModNumTrunks.description: The number of trunks on this module. Note, trunks are links that are, by definition, backbone connections. Examples of trunks are ring in and ring out ports for token ring, and the connections for rings to the backplane.

ocModNumSubSlots.name: ocModNumSubSlots
ocModNumSubSlots.description: The number of possible submodules that can exist in this slot.

olNetDPTable.name: olNetDPTable
olNetDPTable.description: A table that contains information linking physical backplane allocation to logical networks. This information is useful: (1) to determine the physical allocation of networks on the backplane, and (2) to determine the remaining capacity of the backplane for future network growth. Since unknown modules are managed via dip switches, this is useful in order to set the dips to the appropriate settings. Ethernet is a bus architecture. Once a path is allocated, all modules and ports can access that path. Token Ring and FDDI are ring architectures. Each module on a ring requires a path. Therefore, 4 paths could be used to link 4 modules together on one ring, or 2 modules on 2 separate rings. It is possible to have a module allocated to a ring (and thus a data path) without linking to another module. These rules can be used to determine the remaining capacity for network growth.

olNetDPEntry.name: olNetDPEntry
olNetDPEntry.description: A list of information about each data path in the concentrator.

olNetDPDataPath.name: olNetDPDataPath
olNetDPDataPath.description: The data path on the backplane. Data paths between different protocols overlap. That is, an ethernet data path will overlap with multiple token ring and fddi data paths.

olNetDPNetID.name: olNetDPNetID
olNetDPNetID.description: The network that this data path corresponds to. If the data path is not being used at all, notUsed(1) is the return value. If the data path is being used by another protocol, then otherProto(2) is the return value.

olNetSecurityMACTable.name: olNetSecurityMACTable
olNetSecurityMACTable.description: A table of security configuration parameters and MAC addresses associated with every port with security configured in the concentrator.

olNetSecurityMACEntry.name: olNetSecurityMACEntry
olNetSecurityMACEntry.description: A list of security configuration parameters and MAC addresses associated with each port with security configured in the concentrator.

olNetSecurityMACSlotIndex.name: olNetSecurityMACSlotIndex
olNetSecurityMACSlotIndex.description: The slot number that contains this port.

olNetSecurityMACPortIndex.name: olNetSecurityMACPortIndex
olNetSecurityMACPortIndex.description: The port number within this slot.

olNetSecurityMACAddress.name: olNetSecurityMACAddress
olNetSecurityMACAddress.description: The security MAC address assigned to this port.

olNetSecurityMACMode.name: olNetSecurityMACMode
olNetSecurityMACMode.description: The desired security mode for this port/address.

olNetSecurityMACStatus.name: olNetSecurityMACStatus
olNetSecurityMACStatus.description: Each instance of the olNetSecurityMACTable associated with this olNetSecurityMACEntry (slot, port, and address) will be deleted by the agent if this olNetSecurityMACEntry is not equal to valid(1). Initial creation of instances occurs via a set operation on a specific slot/port/address.

olNetOlSecAddrTable.name: olNetOlSecAddrTable
olNetOlSecAddrTable.description: A table of security MAC addresses.

olNetOlSecAddrEntry.name: olNetOlSecAddrEntry
olNetOlSecAddrEntry.description: Security MAC addresses indexed by slot, port, and MAC address.

olNetOlSecAddrSlotIndex.name: olNetOlSecAddrSlotIndex
olNetOlSecAddrSlotIndex.description: The slot number index (used along with the port and address indices).

olNetOlSecAddrPortIndex.name: olNetOlSecAddrPortIndex
olNetOlSecAddrPortIndex.description: The port number index (used along with the slot and address indices).

olNetOlSecAddrAddress.name: olNetOlSecAddrAddress
olNetOlSecAddrAddress.description: The security MAC address index (used along with the slot and port indices). Note that there may be multiple addresses associated with a single port.

olNetOlSecAddrStatus.name: olNetOlSecAddrStatus
olNetOlSecAddrStatus.description: Setting this object to valid(1) will cause the corresponding security MAC address to be associated with the given port. Setting this object to invalid(2) will clear the corresponding MAC address for the given port.

olNetOlSecControlTable.name: olNetOlSecControlTable
olNetOlSecControlTable.description: A table of security configuration parameters pertaining to a specific port.

olNetOlSecControlEntry.name: olNetOlSecControlEntry
olNetOlSecControlEntry.description: Security configuration parameters pertaining to a specific port (indexed by slot and port).

olNetOlSecControlSlotIndex.name: olNetOlSecControlSlotIndex
olNetOlSecControlSlotIndex.description: The slot number index (used along with the port index).

olNetOlSecControlPortIndex.name: olNetOlSecControlPortIndex
olNetOlSecControlPortIndex.description: The port number index (used along with the slot index).

olNetOlSecControlMode.name: olNetOlSecControlMode
olNetOlSecControlMode.description: The desired security mode for this port. Setting this object to enable(1) is equivalent to setting the 'SecType' object (see below) to full(1), since both actions enable Eavesdropping and Intrusion Security.

olNetOlSecControlSecType.name: olNetOlSecControlSecType
olNetOlSecControlSecType.description: Setting this object enables a certain type of security for this port: Eavesdropping Security-only, Intrusion Security-only, or Full. Note that setting this object to full(1) is equivalent to setting the 'Mode' object (see above) to enable(1).

olNetOlSecControlActOnIntr.name: olNetOlSecControlActOnIntr
olNetOlSecControlActOnIntr.description: This object can be used to get or set the port-action-on- intrusion flag on a per-port basis. When an Intrusion Security breach is attempted on a port, the Security Module can automatically disable the port and/or generate a trap to management, as dictated by this flag.

olNetOlSecControlClearAddrs.name: olNetOlSecControlClearAddrs
olNetOlSecControlClearAddrs.description: When this object is set to clear-all-addrs(1) then all of the security MAC addresses associated with this port will be cleared. Note that this will not change the state of the 'Mode' (or any other) object in this table.

olNetOlSecControlAutolearnMask.name: olNetOlSecControlAutolearnMask
olNetOlSecControlAutolearnMask.description: This mask is used when autolearning is performed to determine whether the nMM should learn any security MAC addresses for this port. If this object is set to enable(1) then the nMM will ignore this port during autolearning. Note that autolearning is not supported by the TRMM.

olNetOlSecAutolearnTrigger.name: olNetOlSecAutolearnTrigger
olNetOlSecAutolearnTrigger.description: When this object is set to autolearn(1) then the nMM will capture a snapshot of its MAC address cache for those ports whose 'AutolearnMask' object is disabled(2). This snapshot may be investigated and modified via the 'LearnTable' (see below). The snapshot of addresses may be downloaded to the Security Module via the 'Download' object (see below).

olNetOlSecAutolearnDownload.name: olNetOlSecAutolearnDownload
olNetOlSecAutolearnDownload.description: When this object is set to download-addresses(1) then the nMM will download its snapshot of addresses to the Security Module.

olNetOlSecLearnTable.name: olNetOlSecLearnTable
olNetOlSecLearnTable.description: A table of security MAC addresses which have been autolearned on the nMM by taking a snapshot of its MAC address cache.

olNetOlSecLearnEntry.name: olNetOlSecLearnEntry
olNetOlSecLearnEntry.description: Security MAC addresses which have been autolearned (indexed by slot, port, and address).

olNetOlSecLearnSlotIndex.name: olNetOlSecLearnSlotIndex
olNetOlSecLearnSlotIndex.description: The slot number index (used along with the port and address indices).

olNetOlSecLearnPortIndex.name: olNetOlSecLearnPortIndex
olNetOlSecLearnPortIndex.description: The port number index (used along with the slot and address indices).

olNetOlSecLearnAddress.name: olNetOlSecLearnAddress
olNetOlSecLearnAddress.description: The security MAC address index (used along with the slot and port indices). Note that there may be multiple addresses per port.

olNetOlSecLearnStatus.name: olNetOlSecLearnStatus
olNetOlSecLearnStatus.description: Setting this object to valid(1) will cause the corresponding security MAC address to be included in the snapshot of autolearned addresses. Setting this object to invalid(2) will clear the corresponding MAC address from the snapshot of autolearned addresses.

olNetOlSecIntruderTable.name: olNetOlSecIntruderTable
olNetOlSecIntruderTable.description: A table of entries which describe Intrusion Security breach attempts. This table contains the same info as the following table, the difference being that this table is indexed by time only and the other is indexed by slot. port.time.

olNetOlSecIntruderEntry.name: olNetOlSecIntruderEntry
olNetOlSecIntruderEntry.description: A table of entries which describe Intrusion Security breach attempts. The index is simply the chronological order in which the attempt occurred; e.g. index 1 corresponds to the first intrusion attempt, index 2 to the next one, and so on. Note that the the oldest entry will be deleted automatically when a new entry is added to a full table.

olNetOlSecIntruderChronIndex.name: olNetOlSecIntruderChronIndex
olNetOlSecIntruderChronIndex.description: The chronological index into the Intruder Table. An index of 1 corresponds to the first Intrusion Security breach attempt, an index of 2 corresponds to the next attempt, etc. Note that the oldest entry will be deleted automatically when a new entry is added to a full table.

olNetOlSecIntruderSlot.name: olNetOlSecIntruderSlot
olNetOlSecIntruderSlot.description: The slot number on which the intrusion attempt occurred.

olNetOlSecIntruderPort.name: olNetOlSecIntruderPort
olNetOlSecIntruderPort.description: The port number on which the intrusion attempt occurred.

olNetOlSecIntruderAddress.name: olNetOlSecIntruderAddress
olNetOlSecIntruderAddress.description: The address of the intruder, if known. If it is not known then this object will equal all zeroes.

olNetOlSecIntruderTimeSince.name: olNetOlSecIntruderTimeSince
olNetOlSecIntruderTimeSince.description: The time in hundredths of a second since the Intrusion Security breach attempt took place. For example, if it is equal to 500 ticks then the intrusion attempt occurred 5 seconds ago.

olNetOlSecIntruderDisabled.name: olNetOlSecIntruderDisabled
olNetOlSecIntruderDisabled.description: This object indicates whether the port on which the intrusion attempt took place was automatically disabled.

olNetOlSecPortIntrTable.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrTable
olNetOlSecPortIntrTable.description: A table of entries which describe Intrusion Security breach attempts. This table contains the same info as the previous table, the difference being the indices used to access the data.

olNetOlSecPortIntrEntry.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrEntry
olNetOlSecPortIntrEntry.description: A table of entries which describe Intrusion Security breach attempts. The indices are the slot, port, and chronological order in time of the intrusion attempt.

olNetOlSecPortIntrSlotIndex.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrSlotIndex
olNetOlSecPortIntrSlotIndex.description: The slot number on which the intrusion attempt occurred.

olNetOlSecPortIntrPortIndex.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrPortIndex
olNetOlSecPortIntrPortIndex.description: The port number on which the intrusion attempt occurred.

olNetOlSecPortIntrChronIndex.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrChronIndex
olNetOlSecPortIntrChronIndex.description: The chronological index into the Intruder Table. An index of 1 corresponds to the first Intrusion Security breach attempt for that port, an index of 2 corresponds to the next attempt, etc. Note that the oldest overall entry (regardless of slot and port) will be deleted automatically when a new entry is added to a full table.

olNetOlSecPortIntrAddress.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrAddress
olNetOlSecPortIntrAddress.description: The address of the intruder, if known. If it is not known then this object will equal all zeroes.

olNetOlSecPortIntrTimeSince.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrTimeSince
olNetOlSecPortIntrTimeSince.description: The time in hundredths of a second since the Intrusion Security breach attempt took place. For example, if it is equal to 500 ticks then the intrusion attempt occurred 5 seconds ago.

olNetOlSecPortIntrDisabled.name: olNetOlSecPortIntrDisabled
olNetOlSecPortIntrDisabled.description: This object indicates whether the port on which the intrusion attempt took place was automatically disabled.

olNetOlSecTrapReason.name: olNetOlSecTrapReason
olNetOlSecTrapReason.description: This object is included in security traps to specify the reason for the trap. When this object is read it will represent the reason for the most recently generated security trap. If this object is read before any security traps have been generated then the value not-applicable(1) will be returned.

olEnetStatsTable.name: olEnetStatsTable
olEnetStatsTable.description: A table that contains statistical information about Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) networks.

olEnetStatsEntry.name: olEnetStatsEntry
olEnetStatsEntry.description: A list of statistical information about each Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) network in the concentrator.

olEnetStatsNetID.name: olEnetStatsNetID
olEnetStatsNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this network.

olEnetStatsFramesRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsFramesRcvdOks
olEnetStatsFramesRcvdOks.description: The count of frames that were successfully received by this network. This counter does not include frames received in error.

olEnetStatsOctetsRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsOctetsRcvdOks
olEnetStatsOctetsRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of octets that were successfully received by this network. This counter does not include octets that were part of frames that were received in error.

olEnetStatsMcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsMcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsMcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of multicast frames successfully received by this network.

olEnetStatsBcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsBcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsBcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of broadcast frames successfully received by this network.

olEnetStatsFrameTooLongs.name: olEnetStatsFrameTooLongs
olEnetStatsFrameTooLongs.description: The count of the number of frames received by this network that exceeds the maximum permitted Ethernet (802.3) frame size.

olEnetStatsAlignmentErrors.name: olEnetStatsAlignmentErrors
olEnetStatsAlignmentErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this network that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and that are not an integral number of octets. These frames are not counted in olEnetStatsFCSErrors.

olEnetStatsFCSErrors.name: olEnetStatsFCSErrors
olEnetStatsFCSErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this network that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and are an integral number of octets.

olEnetStatsRunts.name: olEnetStatsRunts
olEnetStatsRunts.description: The count of the number of frames received by this network that are less than 512 bits long.

olEnetStatsLocalColls.name: olEnetStatsLocalColls
olEnetStatsLocalColls.description: The count of the number of times that two or more ports within this concentrator have received traffic simultaneously.

olEnetStatsDropEvents.name: olEnetStatsDropEvents
olEnetStatsDropEvents.description: The total number of events in which frames were dropped due to lack of resources. Note that this number is not necessarily the number of frames dropped; it is just the number of times this condition has been detected.

olEnetStatsModTable.name: olEnetStatsModTable
olEnetStatsModTable.description: A table of statistical information counted for each module in each Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) network.

olEnetStatsModEntry.name: olEnetStatsModEntry
olEnetStatsModEntry.description: A list of statistical information for each port on each Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) network in the concentrator.

olEnetStatsModNetID.name: olEnetStatsModNetID
olEnetStatsModNetID.description: The unique identifier for this network.

olEnetStatsModSlotIndex.name: olEnetStatsModSlotIndex
olEnetStatsModSlotIndex.description: The slot number that contains this module.

olEnetStatsModFramesRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsModFramesRcvdOks
olEnetStatsModFramesRcvdOks.description: The count of frames that were successfully received by this module. This counter does not include frames received in error.

olEnetStatsModOctetsRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsModOctetsRcvdOks
olEnetStatsModOctetsRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of octets that were successfully received by this module. This counter does not include octets that were part of frames that were received in error.

olEnetStatsModMcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsModMcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsModMcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of multicast frames successfully received by this module.

olEnetStatsModBcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsModBcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsModBcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of broadcast frames successfully received by this module.

olEnetStatsModFrameTooLongs.name: olEnetStatsModFrameTooLongs
olEnetStatsModFrameTooLongs.description: The count of the number of frames received by this module that exceeds the maximum permitted Ethernet (802.3) frame size.

olEnetStatsModAlignmentErrors.name: olEnetStatsModAlignmentErrors
olEnetStatsModAlignmentErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this module that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and that are not an integral number of octets. These frames are not counted in olEnetStatsModFCSErrors.

olEnetStatsModFCSErrors.name: olEnetStatsModFCSErrors
olEnetStatsModFCSErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this module that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and are an integral number of octets.

olEnetStatsModRunts.name: olEnetStatsModRunts
olEnetStatsModRunts.description: The count of the number of frames received by this module that are less than 512 bits long.

olEnetStatsPortTable.name: olEnetStatsPortTable
olEnetStatsPortTable.description: A table of statistical information counted for each port in each Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) network.

olEnetStatsPortEntry.name: olEnetStatsPortEntry
olEnetStatsPortEntry.description: A list of statistical information for each port on each Ethernet (IEEE 802.3) network in the concentrator.

olEnetStatsPortNetID.name: olEnetStatsPortNetID
olEnetStatsPortNetID.description: The unique identifier for this network.

olEnetStatsPortSlotIndex.name: olEnetStatsPortSlotIndex
olEnetStatsPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number that contains this port.

olEnetStatsPortIndex.name: olEnetStatsPortIndex
olEnetStatsPortIndex.description: The port number within this slot.

olEnetStatsPortFramesRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsPortFramesRcvdOks
olEnetStatsPortFramesRcvdOks.description: The count of frames that were successfully received by this port. This counter does not include frames received in error.

olEnetStatsPortOctetsRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsPortOctetsRcvdOks
olEnetStatsPortOctetsRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of octets that were successfully received by this port. This counter does not include octets that were part of frames that were received in error.

olEnetStatsPortMcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsPortMcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsPortMcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of multicast frames successfully received by this port.

olEnetStatsPortBcastRcvdOks.name: olEnetStatsPortBcastRcvdOks
olEnetStatsPortBcastRcvdOks.description: The count of the number of broadcast frames successfully received by this port.

olEnetStatsPortFrameTooLongs.name: olEnetStatsPortFrameTooLongs
olEnetStatsPortFrameTooLongs.description: The count of the number of frames received by this port that exceeds the maximum permitted Ethernet (802.3) frame size.

olEnetStatsPortAlignmentErrors.name: olEnetStatsPortAlignmentErrors
olEnetStatsPortAlignmentErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this port that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and that are not an integral number of octets. These frames are not counted in olEnetStatsPortFCSErrors.

olEnetStatsPortFCSErrors.name: olEnetStatsPortFCSErrors
olEnetStatsPortFCSErrors.description: The count of the number of frames received by this port that did not pass the frame check sequence (FCS) check and are an integral number of octets.

olEnetStatsPortRunts.name: olEnetStatsPortRunts
olEnetStatsPortRunts.description: The count of the number of frames received by this port that are less than 512 bits long.

olEnetStatsPortSrcAddrChanges.name: olEnetStatsPortSrcAddrChanges
olEnetStatsPortSrcAddrChanges.description: The count of the number of times that olEnetStatsPortLastSourceAddr { olEnetStatsPortEntry 11 } has changed.

olEnetStatsPortLastSrcAddr.name: olEnetStatsPortLastSrcAddr
olEnetStatsPortLastSrcAddr.description: The last source address seen on this port for this network for the last successfully received frame.

olEnetStatsPortLastErrAddr.name: olEnetStatsPortLastErrAddr
olEnetStatsPortLastErrAddr.description: The value stored in the source address portion of a frame received in error (alignment, FCS, or too long). Since the frame was received in error, there is no guarantee that this is an actual valid address.

olEnetMapTable.name: olEnetMapTable
olEnetMapTable.description: A table that contains a cache of information relating an Ethernet source address with a specific port for a given network. An indication of this source's utilization of the network is also provided.

olEnetMapEntry.name: olEnetMapEntry
olEnetMapEntry.description: A list of information that tracks a source address to a specific port for each network.

olEnetMapNetID.name: olEnetMapNetID
olEnetMapNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this network.

olEnetMapAddress.name: olEnetMapAddress
olEnetMapAddress.description: An Ethernet source address received by this port on this network.

olEnetMapSlotIndex.name: olEnetMapSlotIndex
olEnetMapSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the port that received this address.

olEnetMapPortIndex.name: olEnetMapPortIndex
olEnetMapPortIndex.description: The port number within olEnetMapSlotIndex's slot that received this address.

olEnetMapFrames.name: olEnetMapFrames
olEnetMapFrames.description: An estimated count of the number of frames generated by this address. This count should be interpreted as an indicator, not a true frame count.

olEnetMapOctets.name: olEnetMapOctets
olEnetMapOctets.description: An estimated count of the number of octets generated by this address. This count should be interpreted as an indicator, not a true octet count.

olEnetMapTime.name: olEnetMapTime
olEnetMapTime.description: The time in in hundredths of a second since this address was last seen. For example, if olEnetMapTime is 500 ticks, then this adddress was seen 5 seconds ago.

chipRptrRptrInfoTable.name: chipRptrRptrInfoTable
chipRptrRptrInfoTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the repeater.

chipRptrRptrInfoEntry.name: chipRptrRptrInfoEntry
chipRptrRptrInfoEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a repeater.

chipRptrRptrInfoSlotIndex.name: chipRptrRptrInfoSlotIndex
chipRptrRptrInfoSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrRptrInfoNetID resides. If chipRptrRptrInfoNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrRptrInfoNetID.name: chipRptrRptrInfoNetID
chipRptrRptrInfoNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this repeater.

chipRptrGroupCapacity.name: chipRptrGroupCapacity
chipRptrGroupCapacity.description: The chipRptrGroupCapacity is the number of groups that can be contained within the repeater. Within each managed repeater, the groups are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to chipRptrGroupCapacity. Some groups may not be present in the repeater, in which case the actual number of groups present will be less than chipRptrGroupCapacity. The number of groups present will never be greater than chipRptrGroupCapacity. Note: In practice, this will generally be the number of field-replaceable units (i.e., modules, cards, or boards) that can fit in the physical repeater enclosure, and the group numbers will correspond to numbers marked on the physical enclosure.

chipRptrOperStatus.name: chipRptrOperStatus
chipRptrOperStatus.description: The chipRptrOperStatus object indicates the operational state of the repeater. The chipRptrHealthText object may be consulted for more specific information about the state of the repeater's health. In the case of multiple kinds of failures (e.g., repeater failure and port failure), the value of this attribute shall reflect the highest priority failure in the following order: chipRptrFailure(3) groupFailure(4) portFailure(5) generalFailure(6).

chipRptrHealthText.name: chipRptrHealthText
chipRptrHealthText.description: The health text object is a text string that provides information relevant to the operational state of the repeater. Agents may use this string to provide detailed information on current failures, including how they were detected, and/or instructions for problem resolution. The contents are agent-specific.

chipRptrReset.name: chipRptrReset
chipRptrReset.description: Setting this object to reset(2) causes a transition to the START state of Fig 9-2 in section 9 [IEEE 802.3 Std]. Setting this object to noReset(1) has no effect. The agent will always return the value noReset(1) when this object is read. This action does not reset the management counters defined in this document nor does it affect the portAdminStatus parameters. Included in this action is the execution of a disruptive Self-Test with the following characteristics: a) The nature of the tests is not specified. b) The test resets the repeater but without affecting management information about the repeater. c) The test does not inject packets onto any segment. d) Packets received during the test may or may not be transferred. e) The test does not interfere with management functions. As a result of this action a chipRptrResetEvent trap should be sent.

chipRptrNonDisruptTest.name: chipRptrNonDisruptTest
chipRptrNonDisruptTest.description: Setting this object to selfTest(2) causes the repeater to perform a agent-specific, non- disruptive self-test that has the following characteristics: a) The nature of the tests is not specified. b) The test does not change the state of the repeater or management information about the repeater. c) The test does not inject packets onto any segment. d) The test does not prevent the relay of any packets. e) The test does not interfere with management functions. After performing this test the agent will update the repeater health information and send a chipRptrHealth trap. Setting this object to noSelfTest(1) has no effect. The agent will always return the value noSelfTest(1) when this object is read.

chipRptrTotalPartitionedPorts.name: chipRptrTotalPartitionedPorts
chipRptrTotalPartitionedPorts.description: This object returns the total number of ports in the repeater whose current state meets all three of the following criteria: chipRptrPortOperStatus does not have the value notPresent(3), chipRptrPortAdminStatus is enabled(1), and chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState is autoPartitioned(2).

chipRptrGroupTable.name: chipRptrGroupTable
chipRptrGroupTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the groups of ports.

chipRptrGroupEntry.name: chipRptrGroupEntry
chipRptrGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a single group of ports.

chipRptrGroupSlotIndex.name: chipRptrGroupSlotIndex
chipRptrGroupSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrGroupNetID resides. If chipRptrGroupNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrGroupNetID.name: chipRptrGroupNetID
chipRptrGroupNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this group's repeater.

chipRptrGroupIndex.name: chipRptrGroupIndex
chipRptrGroupIndex.description: This object identifies the group within the repeater for which this entry contains information. This value is never greater than chipRptrGroupCapacity.

chipRptrGroupDescr.name: chipRptrGroupDescr
chipRptrGroupDescr.description: A textual description of the group. This value should include the full name and version identification of the group's hardware type and indicate how the group is differentiated from other groups in the repeater. Plug-in Module, Rev A' or 'Barney Rubble 10BASE-T 4-port SIMM socket Version 2.1' are examples of valid group descriptions. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

chipRptrGroupObjectID.name: chipRptrGroupObjectID
chipRptrGroupObjectID.description: The vendor's authoritative identification of the group. This value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides a straight-forward and unambiguous means for determining what kind of group is being managed. For example, this object could take the value 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242.1.2.14 if vendor 'Flintstones, Inc.' was assigned the subtree 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242, and had assigned the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242.1.2.14 to its 'Wilma Flintstone 6-Port FOIRL Plug-in Module.'

chipRptrGroupOperStatus.name: chipRptrGroupOperStatus
chipRptrGroupOperStatus.description: An object that indicates the operational status of the group. A status of notPresent(4) indicates that the group is temporarily or permanently physically and/or logically not a part of the repeater. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent effectively removes notPresent entries from the table. A status of operational(2) indicates that the group is functioning, and a status of malfunctioning(3) indicates that the group is malfunctioning in some way.

chipRptrGroupLastOperStatusChange.name: chipRptrGroupLastOperStatusChange
chipRptrGroupLastOperStatusChange.description: An object that contains the value of sysUpTime at the time that the value of the chipRptrGroupOperStatus object for this group last changed. A value of zero indicates that the group's oper status has not changed since the agent last restarted.

chipRptrGroupPortCapacity.name: chipRptrGroupPortCapacity
chipRptrGroupPortCapacity.description: The chipRptrGroupPortCapacity is the number of ports that can be contained within the group. Valid range is 1-1024. Within each group, the ports are uniquely numbered in the range from 1 to chipRptrGroupPortCapacity. Note: In practice, this will generally be the number of ports on a module, card, or board, and the port numbers will correspond to numbers marked on the physical embodiment.

chipRptrPortTable.name: chipRptrPortTable
chipRptrPortTable.description: Table of descriptive and status information about the ports.

chipRptrPortEntry.name: chipRptrPortEntry
chipRptrPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a single port.

chipRptrPortSlotIndex.name: chipRptrPortSlotIndex
chipRptrPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrPortNetID resides. If chipRptrPortNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrPortNetID.name: chipRptrPortNetID
chipRptrPortNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this port's repeater.

chipRptrPortGroupIndex.name: chipRptrPortGroupIndex
chipRptrPortGroupIndex.description: This object identifies the group containing the port for which this entry contains information.

chipRptrPortIndex.name: chipRptrPortIndex
chipRptrPortIndex.description: This object identifies the port within the group for which this entry contains information. This value can never be greater than chipRptrGroupPortCapacity for the associated group.

chipRptrPortAdminStatus.name: chipRptrPortAdminStatus
chipRptrPortAdminStatus.reference: Reference IEEE 802.3 Rptr Mgt, 19.2.6.2, aPortAdminState and 19.2.6.3, acPortAdminControl.
chipRptrPortAdminStatus.description: Setting this object to disabled(2) disables the port. A disabled port neither transmits nor receives. Once disabled, a port must be explicitly enabled to restore operation. A port which is disabled when power is lost or when a reset is exerted shall remain disabled when normal operation resumes. When the logical port is actually a daughterboard on the module, the AdminStatus directly relates to the interface mode of the daughterboard. Setting it enabled(1) enables the interface and likewise disabled(2) disables the interface mode. The admin status takes precedence over auto- partition and functionally operates between the auto-partition mechanism and the AUI/PMA. Setting this object to enabled(1) enables the port and exerts a BEGIN on the port's auto-partition state machine. (In effect, when a port is disabled, the value of chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState for that port is frozen until the port is next enabled. When the port becomes enabled, the chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState becomes notAutoPartitioned(1), regardless of its pre-disabling state.)

chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState.name: chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState
chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState.description: The autoPartitionState flag indicates whether the port is currently partitioned by the repeater's auto-partition protection. The conditions that cause port partitioning are specified in partition state machine in Section 9 [IEEE 802.3 Std]. They are not differentiated here.

chipRptrPortOperStatus.name: chipRptrPortOperStatus
chipRptrPortOperStatus.description: This object indicates the port's operational status. The notPresent(3) status indicates the port is physically removed (note this may or may not be possible depending on the type of port.) The operational(1) status indicates that the port is enabled (see chipRptrPortAdminStatus) and working, even though it might be auto-partitioned (see chipRptrPortAutoPartitionState). If this object has the value operational(1) and chipRptrPortAdminStatus is set to disabled(2), it is expected that this object's value will change to notOperational(2) soon after.

chipRptrMonitorRptrTable.name: chipRptrMonitorRptrTable
chipRptrMonitorRptrTable.description: Table of performance and error statistics for the Repeater.

chipRptrMonitorRptrEntry.name: chipRptrMonitorRptrEntry
chipRptrMonitorRptrEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing total performance and error statistics for a repeater.

chipRptrMonitorSlotIndex.name: chipRptrMonitorSlotIndex
chipRptrMonitorSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrMonitorNetID resides. If chipRptrMonitorNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrMonitorNetID.name: chipRptrMonitorNetID
chipRptrMonitorNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this repeater.

chipRptrMonitorTransmitCollisions.name: chipRptrMonitorTransmitCollisions
chipRptrMonitorTransmitCollisions.description: This counter is incremented every time the repeater state machine enters the TRANSMIT COLLISION state from any state other than ONE PORT LEFT (Ref: Fig 9-2, IEEE 802.3 Std). The approximate minimum time for rollover of this counter is 16 hours.

chipRptrMonitorGroupTable.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupTable
chipRptrMonitorGroupTable.description: Table of performance and error statistics for the groups.

chipRptrMonitorGroupEntry.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupEntry
chipRptrMonitorGroupEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing total performance and error statistics for a single group. Regular retrieval of the information in this table provides a means of tracking the performance and health of the networked devices attached to this group's ports. The counters in this table are redundant in the sense that they are the summations of information already available through other objects. However, these sums provide a considerable optimization of network management traffic over the otherwise necessary retrieval of the individual counters included in each sum.

chipRptrMonitorGroupSlotIndex.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupSlotIndex
chipRptrMonitorGroupSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrMonitorGroupNetID resides. If chipRptrMonitorGroupNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrMonitorGroupNetID.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupNetID
chipRptrMonitorGroupNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this group's repeater.

chipRptrMonitorGroupIndex.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupIndex
chipRptrMonitorGroupIndex.description: This object identifies the group within the repeater for which this entry contains information.

chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames
chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalFrames.description: The total number of frames of valid frame length that have been received on the ports in this group. This counter is the summation of the values of the chipRptrMonitorPortReadableFrames counters for all of the ports in the group. This statistic provides one of the parameters necessary for obtaining the packet error rate. The approximate minimum time for rollover of this counter is 80 hours.

chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets
chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalOctets.description: The total number of octets contained in the valid frames that have been received on the ports in this group. This counter is the summation of the values of the chipRptrMonitorPortReadableOctets counters for all of the ports in the group. This statistic provides an indicator of the total data transferred. The approximate minimum time for rollover of this counter is 58 minutes.

chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors.name: chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors
chipRptrMonitorGroupTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors which have occurred on all of the ports in this group. This counter is the summation of the values of the chipRptrMonitorPortTotalErrors counters for all of the ports in the group.

chipRptrMonitorPortTable.name: chipRptrMonitorPortTable
chipRptrMonitorPortTable.description: Table of performance and error statistics for the ports.

chipRptrMonitorPortEntry.name: chipRptrMonitorPortEntry
chipRptrMonitorPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing performance and error statistics for a single port.

chipRptrMonitorPortSlotIndex.name: chipRptrMonitorPortSlotIndex
chipRptrMonitorPortSlotIndex.description: The slot number of the repeater module on which the isolated network identified by chipRptrMonitorPortNetID resides. If chipRptrMonitorPortNetID does not identify an isolated network, then the value of this object is backplane(255).

chipRptrMonitorPortNetID.name: chipRptrMonitorPortNetID
chipRptrMonitorPortNetID.description: The network index that uniquely identifies this port's repeater.

chipRptrMonitorPortGroupIndex.name: chipRptrMonitorPortGroupIndex
